                <note rend="inline" type="source">325.1121 Bethune, Larry K./27: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-02T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 2, 1931—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. Your 33, April 1, midnight. Minister for Foreign Affairs states that
                    incommunicado in Chilean penal law is a proceeding in criminal <pb facs="1051"
                        n="937" xml:id="pg_937"/> investigation and since it is a legal prerogative
                    of the Judge, he alone is competent to apply, suspend or attenuate it and to
                    determine its duration, and that the Executive can not intervene. Endeavor
                    ascertain whether Bethune was held incommunicado by order of the Judge or by
                    order of the police authorities. If the latter, the Department may want to
                    question statement by Minister of Foreign Affairs that the Executive can not
                    intervene in such matters.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
